GUI COMMON ERROR HANDLING

Test Case 1:
Requirement: There should be an error message printed in the textarea in the GUI if the date isn't a valid date.
Test Description: Created a test with a future date.
Input Data: First Name: r, Last Name: p, Dob: 11/7/2023, Amount: 1000, Account Type: Checking
Expected Result : Prints out "DOB invalid: 11/7/2023 cannot be today or a future date!" in textarea.

Test Case 2:
Requirement: There should be an error message printed in the textarea in the GUI if the date isn't a valid date for College Checking.
Test Description: Created a test with empty first name text field.
Input Data: First Name: r, Last Name: p, Dob: 11/2/2023, Amount: 1000, Account Type: College Checking, Campus: NB
Expected Result : Prints out "DOB invalid: 11/2/2023 under 16." in textarea.

Test Case 3:
Requirement: There should be an error message printed in the textarea in the GUI if the date isn't a valid date for College Checking.
Test Description: Created a test with empty first name text field.
Input Data: First Name: r, Last Name: p, Dob: 11/2/1997, Amount: 1000, Account Type: College Checking, Campus: NB
Expected Result : Prints out "DOB invalid: 11/2/1997 over 24." in textarea.
